  ('2026-02-01'::date, 3, 'Delight yourself in the LORD, and he will give you the desires of your heart.'),
  ('2026-02-02'::date, 3, 'But they who wait for the LORD shall renew their strength; they shall mount up with wings like eagles; they shall run and not be weary; they shall walk and not faint.'),
  ('2026-02-03'::date, 3, 'For I know the plans I have for you, declares the LORD, plans for welfare and not for evil, to give you a future and a hope.'),
  ('2026-02-04'::date, 3, 'Come to me, all who labor and are heavy laden, and I will give you rest.'),
  ('2026-02-05'::date, 3, 'Peace I leave with you; my peace I give to you. Not as the world gives do I give to you. Let not your hearts be troubled, neither let them be afraid.'),
  ('2026-02-06'::date, 3, 'And we know that for those who love God all things work together for good, for those who are called according to his purpose.'),
  ('2026-02-07'::date, 3, 'But he said to me, "My grace is sufficient for you, for my power is made perfect in weakness." Therefore I will boast all the more gladly of my weaknesses, so that the power of Christ may rest upon me.'),
  ('2026-02-08'::date, 3, 'But the fruit of the Spirit is love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness, gentleness, self-control; against such things there is no law.'),
  ('2026-02-09'::date, 3, 'Now to him who is able to do far more abundantly than all that we ask or think, according to the power at work within us.'),
  ('2026-02-10'::date, 3, 'And I am sure of this, that he who began a good work in you will bring it to completion at the day of Jesus Christ.'),
  ('2026-02-11'::date, 3, 'So as to walk in a manner worthy of the Lord, fully pleasing to him: bearing fruit in every good work and increasing in the knowledge of God.'),
  ('2026-02-12'::date, 3, 'Rejoice always, pray without ceasing, give thanks in all circumstances; for this is the will of God in Christ Jesus for you.'),
  ('2026-02-13'::date, 3, 'For God gave us a spirit not of fear but of power and love and self-control.'),
  ('2026-02-14'::date, 3, 'Looking to Jesus, the founder and perfecter of our faith, who for the joy that was set before him endured the cross.'),
